    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Sigh, there are too many moving pieces.\n\nThis is because if mpl detects that it is running in an IPython session the auto-redraw logic uses the hooks that IPython provides to get a post-execute hook.  I would bet that in the debugger those hooks are not firing.  In 'plain' python a different mechanism is used to trigger the re-draw (by just calling `draw_idle` every time anything changes and counting on the backend to be sufficiently asynchronous for this to work (which mostly works)). I am slowly coming around to @mdehoon s position that we should always do it the second way.\n\nThis worked in all cases in mpl 1.4.3 because all of the pyplot methods had explicit calls to `draw_idle` in them.  In 1.5.0 we allow the auto-redraw mechanism to take care of that.\n"
  },
