    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@tacaswell sorry this dropped off the radar.\n\nYou're right that IPython post-execute hooks won't execute after debugger input. IPython doesn't really 'know' about the debugger as a specific thing: from IPython's view, whatever triggered the debugger is still executing, and happens to be prompting the user for input. Doing smarter things with the debugger is on the cards, but it's probably not coming up any time soon.\n\nIn the shorter term, we could add hooks that fire when entering and leaving the debugger - mpl could use those to switch the 'plain' redraw logic on and off. That would only work for our own debugger machinery, though - it should cover `ipdb`, but not `pdb`.\n"
  },
